  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And he provided us [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] at one point with Hungarian passports, my mother and my brother and I.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "That's where he saved our lives.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, then finally Mother understood what was going on.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In the picture books, the Hungarian passports.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Lost their validity, I think, three days later.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So just before they had elapsed, we took these things and a few a suitcases, met [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] General [?",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Banitsky ?] in Vienna, and then took the train to Budapest.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Obviously, these passports were also obviously fishy, because we didn't speak a word of Hungarian and also didn't have the financial stamps that were needed at that time, just [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the amount of currency that's allowed to take out.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They had absolutely nothing there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And it took considerable talking of-- of the general to the Hungarian officials in the train to allow the-- to allow us to pass.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
